{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableOutputStreamRef\/writeAsync(buffer:count:ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writeAsync"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"buffer","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer"},{"text":"!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"count"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ioPriority"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"callback"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and will result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"text":" errors.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" larger than "},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will cause a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"invalidArgument","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes written will be passed to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". It is not an error if this is not the same as the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requested size, as it can happen e.g. on a partial I\/O error,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"but generally we try to write as many bytes as requested.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You are guaranteed that this method will never fail with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":" - if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stream"},{"text":" can’t accept more data, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"method will just wait until this changes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any outstanding I\/O request with higher priority (lower numerical"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"value) will be executed before an outstanding request with lower"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"priority. Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"classes. However, if you override one you must override all.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For the synchronous, blocking version of this function, see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_output_stream_write()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that no copy of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buffer"},{"type":"text","text":" will be made, so it must stay valid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"until ","type":"text"},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is called. See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_output_stream_write_bytes_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes version that will automatically hold a reference to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the contents (without copying) for the duration of the call."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableOutputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PollableOutputStreamRef\/OutputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Request an asynchronous write of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" bytes from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buffer"},{"text":" into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the stream. When the operation is finished "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"text":" will be called.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can then call "},{"code":"g_output_stream_write_finish()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to get the result of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO20OutputStreamProtocolPAAE10writeAsync6buffer5count10ioPriority11cancellable8callback8userDataySvSg_S2iAA14CancellableRefVSgySpySo8_GObjectVGSg_SpySo13_GAsyncResultVGSgAKtXCSgAKtF::SYNTHES